Ethnicity View Instructions 9

1.Double click [Ethnicity(group)]

2. Double click cc.CountEntireTable





3. Go to Show Me and select Packed Bubbles

4. Drag _cc.GenderMale>Female Onto Color

5. Edit Color True = Blue, False = Pink




6. Hide the Legend Card

7.    Drag _cc.Black% onto Detail

8.    Drag _cc_Gender=Female into ToolTip




9.    Double Click the Title. Erase the Title. 

10.  Click Insert and select <AGG(_cc.Black%)>

11.   After <AGG(_cc.Black%)> do a space and type Black



12.   Highlight <AGG(_cc.Black%)> and make it Tableau Bold , Font 24, Bold and Grey  black(#333333)

 13.  Highlight Black and make it Tableau Book, Font 18, Bold and Pink(#fe019a).

14.   Highlight All the Text and Center it. Then hit OK.

15.  Click on Entire view




16.   Rename the Sheet to Ethnicity

17.   Double Click the ToolTip. Make sure it looks like the Below. If you are missing any Calculated Fields, then click on the Insert button and select whatever is are missing. Then click OK.

Male: <SUM(_cc_Gender=Male)> 

Female: <SUM(_cc_Gender=Female)>
